WEBVTT

00:00:00.320 --> 00:00:04.480
All right. Good morning, almost

00:00:02.560 --> 00:00:06.879
afternoon, family. Thank you for joining

00:00:04.480 --> 00:00:08.800
us again today. We're going to go

00:00:06.879 --> 00:00:10.240
over some of the things we see in the

00:00:08.800 --> 00:00:11.120
news real quick and then we'll jump in

00:00:10.240 --> 00:00:12.800
the river. We're going to pray for

00:00:11.120 --> 00:00:14.959
President Trump because he's headed to

00:00:12.800 --> 00:00:16.880
Turkey, and we're going to pray for him

00:00:14.960 --> 00:00:19.680
for this meeting, whatever he's

00:00:16.880 --> 00:00:23.038
doing. We're going to cover him,

00:00:19.680 --> 00:00:24.880
his plane, and everything

00:00:23.039 --> 00:00:26.400
he eats; we have to

00:00:24.880 --> 00:00:28.480
cover him in prayer. He'll be there

00:00:26.400 --> 00:00:30.959
for, I think, three days, so we're going

00:00:28.480 --> 00:00:33.280
to cover him the whole time he's there.

00:00:30.960 --> 00:00:35.360
We have assignments, you know,

00:00:33.280 --> 00:00:37.200
and so we're going to pray over our

00:00:35.360 --> 00:00:41.280
nation. But isn't Jesus

00:00:37.200 --> 00:00:44.640
wonderful? There were no major

00:00:41.280 --> 00:00:46.320
shootings or anything for the Fourth

00:00:44.640 --> 00:00:48.079
of July. I don't think we had much;

00:00:46.320 --> 00:00:50.640
I think we only had one little bit of a

00:00:48.079 --> 00:00:53.280
little something, but it was nothing at

00:00:50.640 --> 00:00:55.760
all. The hand of the Lord

00:00:53.280 --> 00:00:58.239
protected our nation, and you could sense

00:00:55.760 --> 00:01:00.480
it as we were praying. There was a disturbance—I

00:00:58.239 --> 00:01:04.158
could feel it very strong

00:01:00.480 --> 00:01:07.280
all afternoon on the 4th, interceding

00:01:04.159 --> 00:01:10.479
